dcterms:description: The QM9 dataset contains quantum chemistry structures and properties of 134,000 stable small organic molecules, which include atoms from the set {C, H, O, N, F}. The molecules are processed to be in the kekulized form with hydrogens removed.
dcterms:title: QM9

dcterms:description: The ZINC250K dataset contains 250,000 drug-like molecules, each consisting of up to 38 atoms. The dataset is used for molecular generation tasks and is a benchmark for evaluating generative models.
dcterms:title: ZINC250K
